  <p>
    I started having conversations with friends who were in the hospitality industry. The conversations spawned many interesting questions that were later reused when conducting the proper user research.
  </p>
  <p>
    Using my data gathered in the second phase I was able to translate them into How Might We's to help me frame the problem properly. After the HMWs were defined I categorised them into three different user groups. The very same users that would be affected by the final design solution.
  </p>
