<div class="text-row reveal">
  <h4 class="f6 tracked black-50 ttu fw4">Conclusions from wireframing</h4>
  <p>
    To reach the goal of helping the waiter become better at their craft the journey is built around giving feedback to each individual waiter.
  </p>
  <p>My research found that most customers are more likely leave reviews or feedback when the experience is either very bad or very good.</p>
  <p class="f3">How do we make sure the feedback is usable for the waiter?</p>
  <p>
    In order for the waiter to receive tangible feedback (without the emotions), we help the customers along the way. Customers are discouraged from leaving raw text comments. Customers are instead presented with a questionnaire with predefined questions that will help the waiter make sense of the feedback.
  </p>
</div>

