<div class="text-row reveal">
  <p>
    Each topic of the questionnaire is crafted carefully to give quantifiable data to the restaurant. For instance if the customer is unhappy with slow service. The customer can select the option which says 'long wait', but they are also encouraged to enter how long they think they waited in minutes. This way the data can tell how long a 'long wait' truly is.
  </p>
  <p>
    A restaurant on the beach may be able to get away with slow service. However, a heavily trafficked city restaurant will need to be quicker. So the data will automatically align the slow service threshold appropriately.
  </p>

</div>

<div class="text-row reveal">
  <h4 class="f6 tracked black-50 ttu fw4">Visual design</h4>
  <p>
    In the visual design phase I started thinking about micro-interactions on a deeper level
  </p>
  <p>
    For instance how could we have the customer to identify a waiter if the profile picture is really vague? The solution was to include short video snippets instead of static pictures. When a waiter is onboarded they upload a short video of themselves that the app translates into a stop motion video. This helps the user further to identify a waiter more easily.
  </p>
</div>

